com.gembox.spreadsheet.internal.styles

Class ColumnRowCellStyleHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gembox.spreadsheet.internal.styles.AbstractStyleHandler
      • com.gembox.spreadsheet.internal.styles.ColumnRowCellStyleHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AlignmentDataFormatHandler, BorderHandler, CellFormatDataFormatHandler, FillDataFormatHandler, FontDataFormatHandler, FormatHandler, NumberDataFormatHandler, ProtectionDataFormatHandler, StyleHandler
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CellStyleHandler, ColumnRowStyleHandler

    public abstract class ColumnRowCellStyleHandler
extends AbstractStyleHandler
    Represents a base style handler for columns, rows and cells.

    It delegates calls to row's / column's / cell's merged range style handler or to row's / column's cell range style handler.

    It also implements border resolution based on neighbor columns / rows / cells.

    • Method Detail

      • getBaseHandler

        protected abstract AbstractStyleHandler getBaseHandler()
        Gets the base handler for a column, row or cell.
        Returns:
        The base handler for a column, row or cell.

        If column / row / cell is a part of a merged range, then base handler is merged range style handler.

        Otherwise, if column / row is not a part of a merged range, base handler is column's / row's cells range style handler.

        Otherwise, if cell is not a part of a merged range, base handler is null.

      • getCellFormat

        public final CellFormatData getCellFormat()
        Description copied from class: AbstractStyleHandler

        Gets the resolved cell formatting.

        Returned value is never null and modifying it won't make any changes in the underlying storage (it is either cached or cloned version of formatting from the underlying storage or it is dynamically created).

        Overrides:
        getCellFormat in class AbstractStyleHandler
        Returns:
        The resolved cell formatting.

      • setCellFormat

        public final void setCellFormat(CellFormatData value)
        Description copied from class: AbstractStyleHandler
        Sets the cell formatting.

        Input cell formatting can be null, in which case it is replaced with empty formatting associated with the handler's workbook (default cell formatting which inherits all from 'Normal' style).

        If input cell formatting is from the another workbook or it is not attached to any workbook, it is imported.

        Input cell formatting is either cached / frozen or cloned (modifying it later won't make any changes in the underlying storage).

        Overrides:
        setCellFormat in class AbstractStyleHandler
        Parameters:
        value - The cell formatting.
